 buddy SetSpinner newvalue;spinner;minmax
 ‚çù When a potential buddy object's contents change, call this routine to update the associated Spinner (if it has one)
 ‚çù Disregard wrapping when specifying a new value directly

 :If 9=buddy.‚éïNC'_buddy_' ‚çù Is there a Spinner buddying-up to this object?
     spinner‚Üêbuddy._buddy_
 :AndIf 16‚àä##.##.##.BitVals spinner ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_style' 0 ‚çù Are buddies supposed to auto-update back here?
 :AndIf ~'SetBuddy'‚äÇ‚çõ‚àä5‚Üë‚éïSI ‚çù If we're immediately being called "recursively" from ‚àáSetBuddy, then don't do anything!
     :If ##.##.##.IsChar newvalue
         :If (,1)‚â¢‚äÉnewvalue‚Üê‚éïVFI'¬Ø'@{‚çµ='-'}newvalue~',' ‚çù Do we have a single valid number (after cleaning decorations)?
         :OrIf ~##.##.##.IsInt newvalue‚Üê2‚äÉnewvalue ‚çù That translates to an integer?
             :Return ‚çù If we don't have a number, we can't do anything
         :EndIf
     :EndIf
     minmax‚Üêspinner ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_range'(0 100) ‚ãÑ minmax‚Üêminmax[‚çãminmax]
     newvalue‚Üêminmax[1]‚åàminmax[2]‚åänewvalue ‚çù Constrain new value to remain within application's range
     spinner ##.##.##.‚àÜWS‚äÇ'Thumb'newvalue
     ‚çù We do not also fire the Spinner's Change event at this time
 :EndIf


‚çù These buddy controls need to also update my Thumb value here, from the following sources:
‚çù   Class       APL+Win/property    Dyalog
‚çù   -----       -------/--------    ------
‚çù   Edit        Change  text        KeyPress
‚çù   RichEdit    Change  [sel]text   KeyPress
‚çù   Combo       Change  text/value  KeyPress/Select
‚çù   List        Click   value       Select
‚çù   Label               caption
‚çù   Button              caption
‚çù   Check               caption
‚çù   Option              caption
‚çù   Frame               caption
